==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pointal
<hw>Point"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Point</er>:
cf. F. <ets>pointal</ets> an upright wooden prop, OF.
<ets>pointille</ets> a prick or prickle.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The pistil of a plant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of pencil or style used with the tablets of
the Middle Ages.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A pair of tablets [<it>i. e.</it>,
tablets] . . . and a <xex>pointel</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>See <er>Poyntel</er>.</def>
<mark>[Obs. or R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Point alphabet</ent>⟦br⟧
